*{{ill|lt=Mamoru Kiguchi|Q11518230|WD=Q11518230|1=Mamoru Kiguchi}} - raised as ujiko of this shrine; founder of {{ill|lt=World Co., Ltd.|Q8035551|WD=Q8035551|1=World Co.}}. Continued donations and worship after founding his company; a stone monument in the precinct records this.
*{{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Tenpuku Zenji|1=UNKNOWN}} - the area around this shrine is called Yokota and is both birthplace and final place of Zen monk {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Daiki Zenji|1=UNKNOWN}}, active in the {{ill|lt=Sengoku period|Q204023|WD=Q204023|1=Sengoku period}}. The temple north of this shrine is where he trained in childhood.

